      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tires and Tobacco</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Norbert Hirschhorn letter on Sept 7 article on tire hazards urges Congress to react as strongly to threat posed by cigarettes</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''More Indications Hazards of Tires Were Long Known'' (front page, Sept. 7):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''More Indications Hazards of Tires Were Long Known'' (front page, Sept. 7):</p>
        <p>You quote Senator Richard C. Shelby, Republican of Alabama, as saying, ''Ford and Firestone had at a minimum a moral obligation to make sure that the products they sell to the American public and other people in other countries are safe.'' He added, ''And yet they both failed to bring this issue to consumers' and the federal government's attention, at the cost of dozens of lives.''</p>
        <p>Will Congress now also react strenuously to the manufacturers of cigarettes, responsible for taking hundreds of thousands of lives each year in the United States and millions overseas?</p>
        <p>NORBERT HIRSCHHORN, M.D.  New York, Sept. 8, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a consultant to the World Health Organization on tobacco control.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
